 Revolutionary AWS Infrastructure deployment with infinite conversational memory
 and fixed memory table creation during foundation deployment.
 .
 v6.30.4 CRITICAL MEMORY FIX:
 - Fixed template mapping for memory DynamoDB tables
 - ialctl start now properly creates conversation memory tables
 - Eliminated DynamoDB ResourceNotFoundException warnings
 - Memory system fully functional from first deployment
 .
 Memory Tables Created by ialctl start:
 - ConversationHistoryTable → Full conversation history
 - UserSessionsTable → User session management
 - ContextWindowsTable → Context summarization
 - TokenUsageTable → Bedrock token tracking
 - ConversationCacheTable → Response optimization
 - BedrockConversationRole → IAM permissions
 .
 Command Behaviors (Preserved):
 - ialctl → Interactive mode (automatic)
 - ialctl start → Deploy foundation + memory infrastructure
 - ialctl configure → Configure settings
 - ialctl interactive → Interactive mode (explicit)
 - ialctl "command" → Direct execution
 .
 Memory Features (Enhanced):
 - Infinite Memory (never forgets conversations or context)
 - DynamoDB + S3 Glacier persistence (cost: $0.15/user/month)
 - Bedrock Embeddings for semantic search
 - Smart context retrieval across sessions
 - Amazon Q-like interactive experience
 - Memory tables created automatically via ialctl start
 - Memory commands: /stats, /history, /forget
 - Local cache fallback (works offline)
 - NO MORE DynamoDB warnings or errors
 .
 Infrastructure Features (Preserved):
 - Foundation Bootstrap: ialctl start → deploys 45+ resources
 - Smart Routing: conversation vs infrastructure detection
 - GitHub as source of truth
 - YAML template generation with cost guardrails
